{
  "local_port": 44068,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I have a problem with coupon set up. I have created a coupon in WooCommerce and I want it to be applied to the product on sale. I have also removed the check from the exclude sale item. But still it's not applying that coupon to products which are on sale. How can I fix it?",
  "response": "If you've created a coupon in WooCommerce and are having trouble applying it to sale items even after unchecking the \"Exclude sale items\" option, here are some steps to troubleshoot and resolve the issue:\n\n1. **Check Coupon Restrictions**: \n   - Go to **WooCommerce > Coupons** and edit the coupon you've created.\n   - Ensure that you have both the **Usage Restrictions** and **Usage Limits** configured appropriately. Double-check that you're not unintentionally imposing any conditions that might be blocking the coupon from being applied.\n\n2. **Confirm Product Settings**:\n   - Make sure the products that are on sale have the correct **Sale Price** set. In the product edit screen, check that the sale price is less than the regular price.\n\n3. **Review Coupon Type**:\n   - Ensure that the coupon type (fixed cart discount, fixed product discount, or percent discount) you have chosen aligns with the product you are trying to apply it to. If a coupon type conflicts with your product setting, it might not apply.\n\n4. **Clear Cache**:\n   - If you are using caching plugins or server-side caching, clear the cache. Caching can sometimes prevent newly created coupons or changes in WooCommerce from being visible immediately.\n\n5. **Test in Incognito/Private Mode**:\n   - Sometimes, cookies or session issues in your browser could affect coupon application. Open an incognito/private window and try applying the coupon there to see if it works.\n\n6. **Check Theme and Plugin Conflicts**:\n   - Temporarily switch to a default WordPress theme (like Twenty Twenty-Three). If the coupon works in the default theme, there may be an issue with your current theme.\n   - Deactivate other plugins one by one to identify if there's a conflict causing the issue. \n\n7. **WooCommerce Status**:\n   - Navigate to **WooCommerce > Status** and check for any error messages or notices that could indicate what might be wrong with coupon application.\n\n8. **Update WooCommerce**:\n   - Ensure that your WooCommerce plugin and WordPress are up to date. Bugs are often fixed in new releases.\n\n9. **Debugging**:\n   - You can enable debugging in WooCommerce to see if any errors are recorded when applying the coupon. This could provide insight into why the coupon isn\u2019t applying.\n\n10. **Console Errors**:\n    - Open the browser's developer console (usually F12) while on the checkout page to see if any JavaScript errors are displayed that might be affecting coupon functionality.\n\nIf, after following these steps, the coupon is still not working, consider reaching out to WooCommerce support or checking the WooCommerce community forums for additional assistance.",
